 Types of functions in Python.

1)With no argument and no return value.
2)With no argument and with a Return value.
3)Argument and No Return value.
4)With argument and return value.


From the above, 1 and 3 types of functions in Python do not return any value when they are called.
So, while defining them, we can avoid the return keyword. When we call the 2 and 4 types of functions, they return some value. 
So, we have to use the return keyword.







